Treasury Secretary James Baker tolda Senate Appropriations subcommittee there is still lots ofroom for improvement in government programs to crack down ontax cheating.    "I think we're far from the point at which we reachsaturation," Baker said when asked at what point additionalefforts to catch cheating become fruitless.    He said Internal Revenue Service efforts would raise aprojected 41 billion dlrs in fiscal 1988 compared to 18 billiondlrs in 1981.    "So we are increasing," Baker said. Reuter&#3;